          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The outgoing charged particles were registered",
                "by a charged-particle spectrometer allowing the",
                "measurement of both energy and angular distributions",
                "of outgoing particles. Particle masses are determined",
                "by measuring both the energy deposited in Si",
                "detectors and the time of flight with a 2 m flight",
                "path. Neutrons are registered by liquid scintillators",
                "set up at the distance of about 7 m from the target.",
                "The pulsed beam and time of flight technique are used",
                "to determine the energies of outgoing neutrons. The",
                "particles are mostly registered at backward angles to",
                "reduce direct reaction contributions."
              ]
            }
          ],
